    <string name="text_caesar_explanation">
        The caesar cipher is credited as the first shift cipher. It is named after Roman emperor
        Julius Caesar, who used the cipher for his private messages. The Caesar cipher works by
        shifting a given character three spaces to the right. For example, the letter B would become
        the letter E.
